As of today, the total number of confirmed Covid-19 cases
in South Africa is 14 355. There are new 831 reported positive cases today. Health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize reported a total number
of 261 deaths. The country has also seen 6478 thus far. Western Cape is leading with 3097 positive cases and 149
deaths. Second is Gauteng with 1583 cases and 25 deaths, followed
by Kwazulu-Natal with 806 cases and 45 deaths. Eastern Cape is fourth with 746 cases and 32 deaths.  